# EPM Infrastructure Rules

## The Absolute Rule

```
Local workstation: git add, git commit, git push — NOTHING ELSE
All execution:     GitHub Actions (cloud) or Netcup VPS via SSH

Note: When running directly on the VPS, deployment is done via docker compose.
See .context/AGENT.md for the authoritative deployment procedure.
```

## GitHub Actions — SSH Heredoc Must Be Quoted

```yaml
# ✅ CORRECT — variables resolve on remote server
- name: Deploy
  uses: appleboy/ssh-action@master
  with:
    script: |
      cd /root/openagile/egbuna_estate_account_streamlight/estate-portfolio
      git pull origin main
      docker compose up -d epm_v2

# If writing raw heredoc in shell step:
# ✅ CORRECT — single-quoted delimiter
run: |
  ssh user@host << 'ENDSSH'
    cd /path && docker compose up -d
  ENDSSH

# ❌ WRONG — unquoted, variables resolve on runner not server
run: |
  ssh user@host << ENDSSH
    cd $HOME/openagile && docker compose up -d
  ENDSSH
```

## CI Pipeline — Fast Path vs Full Path

```yaml
# Fast path (feature/**, develop): static analysis + build + staging deploy
# Full path (main, test, schedule, workflow_dispatch): full pyramid

# Gate condition for expensive stages:
if: |
  github.ref == 'refs/heads/main' ||
  github.ref == 'refs/heads/test' ||
  github.event_name == 'schedule' ||
  github.event.inputs.full_suite == 'true'
```

## Docker — Never New Postgres Container

```yaml
# ✅ CORRECT — reuse shared postgres
services:
  backend:
    networks:
      - openagile_network

networks:
  openagile_network:
    external: true   # ← MUST be external, not created here

# ❌ WRONG — creating a new postgres
services:
  db:
    image: postgres:15
    # This will conflict with shared openagile_postgres
```

## Docker — Frontend Build in GitHub Actions, Not on VPS

```yaml
# GitHub Actions workflow:
- name: Build React SPA
  run: |
    cd estate-portfolio-manager
    npm ci
    npm run build

- name: Copy into backend static dir
  run: cp -r estate-portfolio-manager/dist/. backend/app/static/

- name: Build Docker image
  run: docker build -t epm-backend ./backend
# The image already contains the built React files — no npm on VPS
```

## Docker — Always --no-cache for Frontend Hotfixes

```bash
# ✅ On VPS when deploying frontend UI changes
docker compose build --no-cache epm

# Regular backend-only changes can use cached build
docker compose build epm
```

## Traefik Labels — Always Include All Required Labels

```yaml
# ✅ CORRECT — full label set required
labels:
  - "traefik.enable=true"
  - "traefik.http.routers.SERVICE.rule=Host(`SUBDOMAIN.zubbystudio.shop`)"
  - "traefik.http.routers.SERVICE.entrypoints=websecure"
  - "traefik.http.routers.SERVICE.tls=true"
  - "traefik.http.routers.SERVICE.tls.certresolver=letsencrypt"
  - "traefik.http.services.SERVICE.loadbalancer.server.port=PORT"
  - "traefik.docker.network=openagile_network"
```

## GitHub Secrets — Never Hardcode

```yaml
# ✅ CORRECT — all credentials from secrets
env:
  DB_HOST: ${{ secrets.DB_HOST }}
  DB_PASSWORD: ${{ secrets.DB_PASSWORD }}
  JWT_SECRET: ${{ secrets.JWT_SECRET }}

# ❌ WRONG — hardcoded credentials
env:
  DB_PASSWORD: "mypassword123"
```

## Required GitHub Secrets Reference

```
VPS_HOST, VPS_USER, VPS_SSH_KEY
JWT_SECRET
DB_HOST, DB_NAME, DB_USER, DB_PASSWORD, DB_PORT
DB_TEST_SCHEMA (= estate_portfolio_test)
ADMIN_USERNAME, ADMIN_PASSWORD (EPM admin credentials)
E2E_ADMIN_USER, E2E_ADMIN_PASS, E2E_VIEWER_USER, E2E_VIEWER_PASS
SNYK_TOKEN
```

## Vault Sync — Reuse Existing SSH Key

```
DO NOT generate a new SSH key for vault sync.
Reuse the existing VPS key (id_ed25519 or equivalent).
Add existing public key to private vault repo deploy keys (read-only).
vault-sync.yml uses: key: ${{ secrets.VPS_SSH_KEY }}  (same secret)
```
